orking full-time, Aaron enrolled in a graduate degree program at American University in Washington, D.C. He used the coalition-building and bipartisan cooperation experience he had gained on Capitol Hill to bring a unique perspective to his studies. In 2008, Aaron graduated from American University with Master‚Äôs Degree in U.S. Foreign Policy. He currently resides in Arlington, Virginia where he works as a Congressional Analyst for Dynetics Inc and is an active member of the Arlington Ridge Civic Association, VFW Post 3150, and the Committee for a Better Arlington.','The Leadership Institute','https://www.leadershipinstitute.org/training/contact.cfm?FacultyID=477755',NULL,'Ringel',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
