Ambassador Nagy arrived in the United States in 1957 as a political refugee from Hungary; he received his B.A. from Texas Tech University and M.S.A. from George Washington University.','U.S. Department of State','https://www.state.gov/r/pa/ei/biog/284402.htm',NULL,'Nagy',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
    ('3016','Defense','Milan Nikolich','Director of Defense Research and Engineering for Research and Technology',NULL,NULL,'179700','2018-08-13 00:00:00',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,13,'milan-nikolich',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'defense',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Dr. Milan ‚ÄúMitch‚Äù Nikolich is the Director of Defense Research and Engineering for Research and Technology and serves as the principal advisor to the Under Secretary of Defense for Research and Engineering on all of the Department‚Äôs research and technology investments. He also serves as the Mission Area Advisor for National Defense Strategy technology development implementation and oversees activities in Microelectronics, Cyber, Quantum Science, Directed Energy and Machine Learning/Artificial Intelligence. He establishes the Department‚Äôs annual strategic Science and Technology investment strategy, issues policy and guidance for aligning the Department‚Äôs Science and Technology investment to this strategy, and conducts reviews to ensure progress toward the Department‚Äôs goals.

