    ('139','Consumer Product Safety Commission','Patricia Hines Adkins','Executive Director',NULL,NULL,'$126,148-$189,600',NULL,NULL,'https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4388310-Patricia-Hines-Adkins-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,71,'patricia-hines-adkins','True',NULL,NULL,NULL,'consumer-product-safety-commission',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'In September 2014, Patricia H. Adkins was appointed by the U.S. Consumer Product Safety Commission (CPSC) as its Executive Director,  Ms. Adkins is responsible for managing the agency‚Äôs $125 million public health and safety budget and more than 500 employees.  She also served the Commission for more than seven years as the Chief of Staff to former Chairman Ann Brown. For more than 30 years, Ms. Adkins has held leadership positions in public health, injury prevention, business operations, and public policy with organizations such as Purdue Pharma L.P., the Children‚Äôs National Medical Center‚Äôs Safe Kids Worldwide, and the Home Safety Council. Ms. Adkins earned her B.A. and M.B.A from Howard University in Washington, D.C.','2018 ICPHSO Annual Meeting and Training Symposium','https://2018icphsoannualmeetingandtraini.sched.com/speaker/patriciaadkins2',NULL,'Adkins',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
    ('965','Commerce','Brian Lenihan','Deputy Assistant Secretary for Legislative and Intergovernmental Affairs',NULL,NULL,'153000','2017-04-10 00:00:00','2018-03-17 00:00:00','https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4388354-Brian-Lenihan-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'brian-lenihan','True',NULL,NULL,NULL,'commerce',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/bjlenihan/','The Associated General Contractors of America has built out their lobby shop with the addition of Brian Lenihan as Director of Tax, Fiscal Affairs & Accounting. Lenihan, who recently departed the office of Congressman Diane Black (R-Tenn.), a member of the Ways & Means and House Budget Committee, will focus on issues pertaining to tax reform, the ongoing debate over debt reduction and accounting matters, among others. Lenihan, a Capitol Hill and K Street veteran, previously worked the Hill from the outside at the lobbying law firm Williams & Jensen PLLC, tending to a number of clients in the health, defense, energy, and financial services sectors. He also lobbied on behalf of the American International Automobile Dealers Association on tax and trade issues. And his congressional experience includes work with the leadership offices of then-House Majority Whip Roy Blunt (R-Mo.) and House Republican Conference Chairwoman Deborah Pryce (R-Ohio). Lenihan resides in Alexandria, Va. with his wife and son.','Associated General Contractors of America via Internet Archive','https://web.archive.org/save/https://www.agc.org/news/2013/04/11/lenihan-joins-agc-congressional-relations-team',NULL,'Lenihan',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
    ('2612','Commerce','Mira Radielovic Ricardel','Senior Advisor to the Secretary','Under Secretary of Commerce for Industry and Security',NULL,NULL,'2017-06-18 00:00:00','2018-04-28 00:00:00','https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4388478-Mira-Radielovic-Ricardel-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'mira-radielovic-ricardel-commerce',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'commerce',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/mira-ricardel-08b529b6/','She has had an extensive career in the national security arena in both the public and private sectors. Within the Department of Defense, Ms. Ricardel held the positions of Acting Assistant Secretary of Defense and Principal Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for International Security policy and Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Eurasia, and was awarded the Department of Defense Medal for Distinguished Public Service. Ms. Ricardel also served as Legislative Assistant for Arms Control and Foreign Policy to Republican Leader Bob Dole. From 2006‚Äì2015, Ms. Ricardel held senior leadership positions within Boeing Defense Space and Security, most recently Vice President, International Business Development, Network & Space Systems, where she led the business unit‚Äôs marketing and growth strategies for international markets. She holds a Bachelor of Science in Foreign Service from Georgetown University and completed doctoral course work at the Fletcher School of Law and Diplomacy.','White House','https://web.archive.org/web/20180119203019/https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/president-donald-j-trump-announces-key-administration-posts-2/',NULL,'Ricardel',NULL,NULL,'White House Office',NULL,NULL),
    ('1033','Defense','James E. McPherson','General Counsel of the Army',NULL,NULL,NULL,'2017-12-20 00:00:00',NULL,'https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4387644-James-E-McPherson-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,13,'james-e-mcpherson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'defense',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'James E. McPherson of Virginia to be General Counsel, Department of the Army. Mr. McPherson most recently served as the executive director of the National Association of Attorneys General, one of the oldest legal associations in the country, where he leads the professional association of the state, territorial, and District of Columbia Attorneys General. Mr. McPherson previously served as the General Counsel of the Department of Defense Counterintelligence Field Activity. A retired Rear Admiral, Mr. McPherson‚Äôs final assignment was as the 39th Judge Advocate General of the Navy. He first gained military experience as an enlisted member of the United States Army, later being commissioned as an Ensign in the Judge Advocate General‚Äôs Corps. Mr. McPherson is a recipient of the Distinguished Service Medal, the Legion of Merit, and the Meritorious Service Medal. He received his master of laws degree from the Judge Advocate General‚Äôs School of the Army, his juris doctor from the University of San Diego, School of Law, and his bachelors in public administration from San Diego State University.','White House','https://www.whitehouse.gov/presidential-actions/president-donald-j-trump-announces-intent-nominate-personnel-key-administration-posts-24/',NULL,'McPherson',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
