    ('48','Environmental Protection Agency','Douglas Ericksen','Senior Advisor',NULL,NULL,'161900','2017-01-21 00:00:00','2017-05-20 00:00:00','https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/3766132-Ericksen-Doug.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,63,'douglas-ericksen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'environmental-protection-agency',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Born and raised in Whatcom County, Doug Ericksen has been bringing hometown values and solutions to Olympia since 1998. After serving six terms in the House, he was elected to the Senate in 2010. Senator Ericksen represents Whatcom County‚Äôs 42nd District, from Bellingham to the Canadian border. Senator Ericksen is ranking minority member on the Senate Energy, Environment and Technology Committee. He also serves on the Higher Education and Workforce Development Committee. His legislative priorities include providing solutions to keep energy prices low, create jobs and enhance our quality of life. Doug received a bachelor‚Äôs degree from Cornell University and a master‚Äôs from Western Washington University. He and his wife Tasha, a high-school teacher, are raising their two daughters in Ferndale.','Washington State Republican Caucus','http://dougericksen.src.wastateleg.org/about-me-2/',NULL,'Ericksen',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
