    ('960','Commerce','Clay Kiefaber','Senior Advisor to the Chief Financial Officer and Assistant Secretary for Administration',NULL,NULL,'172100','2017-01-31 00:00:00','2017-05-26 00:00:00','https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4388355-Clay-Kiefaber-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'clay-kiefaber',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'commerce',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/clay-kiefaber-abab4483/','Mr. Clay H. Kiefaber served as the President of Colfax Corporation from January 2010 to April 2012. Mr. Kiefaber serves as Acting Chief Executive Officer of ESAB Group (UK) Ltd. He served as an Acting Chief Executive Officer of ESAB at Colfax Corporation from January 2012 to August 19, 2015. He served as the Chief Executive Officer of Colfax Corporation since January 2010 until December 31, 2015. He served as a Group President of the architectural coatings and windows group of Masco Corporation from December 9, 2005 to 2007 and served as its Group Vice President of Builder Cabinet Group since December 19, 2003. He served as President of Merillat Industries LLC since 1998. He joined Merillat Industries in 1989 as Director of Just-In-Time Planning, he served in a variety of operations management positions including Vice President of Manufacturing, Vice President of Operations and Executive Vice President. Prior to Merillat, Mr. Kiefaber was with Price Waterhouse (now PricewaterhouseCoopers) serving as a Senior Manager in its Advanced Manufacturing Group. He also held sales and marketing positions with Harris Corporation, Hewlett-Packard and Digital Equipment Corporation. He served as a Director for Colfax Corporation from May 7, 2008 to August 19, 2015. He serves as President of the Boys and Girls Club of Lenawee County and is active with Junior Achievement. Mr. Kiefaber holds a Bachelor of Arts in Political Science from Miami of Ohio in 1978 and a Master''s of Business Administration from the University of Colorado in 1981.','Bloomberg','https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=6316747&privcapId=617309',NULL,'Kiefaber',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
    ('1013','Defense','Charles Frederick Drummond','Deputy Assistant Secretary of Defense for Force Education and Training',NULL,NULL,'158297','2017-08-28 00:00:00',NULL,'https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4388363-Charles-Frederick-Drummond-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,13,'charles-frederick-drummond',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'defense',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/fred-drummond-9384aa120/','Prior to joining OSD, Mr. Drummond was responsible for Navy‚Äôs strategy, policy, resource allocation and execution oversight for all officer, graduate, and voluntary education programs on behalf of the Deputy Chief of Naval Operations (Manpower, Personnel, Training and Education) (N1). A career Naval Officer, Mr. Drummond served in a variety of operational and staff billets. As a Naval Flight Officer flying in the EA-6B and in the USAF EF-111A, Mr. Drummond deployed across the globe conducting combat and peacetime operations. Non-operational tours included assignments in education, training and manpower. Mr. Drummond‚Äôs military awards include the Defense Superior Service Medal, the Legion of Merit, the Distinguished Flying Cross, and the Air Medal (1 individual and 7 Strike/Flight). He is a graduate of Virginia Tech and received a Master‚Äôs of Political Science from Auburn University of Montgomery','Department of Defense','https://web.archive.org/web/20180123185336/https://www.defense.gov/News/News-Releases/News-Release-View/Article/1286083/senior-executive-service-announcements/',NULL,'Drummond',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
    ('1016','Defense','William Sherman Castle','Principal Deputy General Counsel',NULL,NULL,'179700','2017-08-27 00:00:00',NULL,'https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4388360-William-Sherman-Castle-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,13,'william-sherman-castle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'defense',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/william-s-castle-esq-9b16ab52/','Previously, Mr. Castle was Minority General Counsel to the Senate Armed Services Committee, Chief Counsel in Senator Orrin Hatch''s Office of the Senate President Pro Tempore, and Senator Hatch‚Äôs Senior National Security Counsel. Mr. Castle received his Bachelor of Arts in Political Science from Brown University in 1993 and his Juris Doctorate from the University of Pennsylvania Law School in 1999. His work has been published in the Harvard Journal of Law and Public Policy. Mr. Castle is admitted to practice law in New Jersey and the District of Columbia.','Department of Defense','https://web.archive.org/save/https://www.defense.gov/About/Biographies/Biography-View/Article/1316044/william-s-castle/',NULL,'Castle',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
