    ('2402','Defense','Jonathan Lloyd Ullyot','Special Assistant, Office of the Assistant Secretary of Defense for Public Affairs',NULL,NULL,'161900','2017-01-20 00:00:00','2017-04-11 00:00:00','https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/3766245-Ullyot-Jonathan.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,13,'jonathan-lloyd-ullyot-defense',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'defense',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/john-ullyot-a9561510b/','Mr. Ullyot has over two decades‚Äô experience in strategic counsel, media relations and issues management in the public and private sectors. He has led strategic engagements with some of the world‚Äôs most respected companies and CEOs on many high-profile issues, including major product recalls, earnings, mergers, litigation, regulatory scrutiny, and Congressional testimony. Mr. Ullyot served for seven years on the staff of the United States Senate as a senior policy advisor for two veteran U.S. Senators and as communications director for two Senate Committees, Veterans'' Affairs and Armed Services. In the private sector, he was vice president of corporate communications for AOL Europe, Washington spokesman for Intel, and a longtime senior communications counselor at several top public relations firms including Hill+Knowlton Strategies and Brighton Strategy Group. Mr. Ullyot received his Bachelor of Arts in Government-International Relations from Harvard University, and served as an Intelligence Officer and Scout Sniper Platoon Commander in the United States Marine Corps.','LinkedIn','https://www.linkedin.com/in/john-ullyot-a9561510b/',NULL,'Ullyot',NULL,NULL,'Veterans Affairs',NULL,NULL),
    ('704','Labor','John K. Mashburn','Deputy Assistant Secretary for OCIA',NULL,NULL,'179700','2017-07-18 00:00:00',NULL,'https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4388014-John-Mashburn-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,14,'john-k-mashburn','True',NULL,NULL,NULL,'labor',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Mashburn',NULL,NULL,NULL,'John K. Mashburn was a deputy cabinet secretary, who helps oversee the White House liaisons acting as the president‚Äôs eyes and ears at dozens of federal agencies. Mashburn, a prominent social conservative and congressional aide to the late Sen. Jesse Helms, worked for the Trump campaign as a policy director starting in April 2016. He also received $7,341 in consulting fees from the American Civil Rights Union this spring while he was employed by the White House. Started by a former Reagan administration official as a check to the American Civil Liberties Union, the nonprofit ACRU ‚Äúmonitors and counters organizations that threaten our constitutional rights and promotes election integrity,‚Äù among others things, according to its website.',NULL),
    ('828','Commerce','Brendan McCommas','Chief of Staff','Senior Advisor, Patent and Trademark Office','Senior Advisor, Office Of Legislative And Intergovernmental Affairs','160000','2017-01-31 00:00:00',NULL,'https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/3890946-Brendan-Mccommas.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'brendan-mccommas',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'commerce',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/brendan-mccommas-27467357/','Brendan McCommas is the Acting Chief of Staff for the United States Patent and Trademark Office (USPTO). He previously served as a Special Assistant to the Secretary of Commerce and Senior Advisor to the Director of the USPTO. He also served as a patent examiner in Technology Center 2600. As the Director‚Äôs principal advisor, the Chief of Staff helps coordinate a $3.2B budget, in support of the bureau‚Äôs 12,000 employees to execute the daily operations, policies, priorities, and global communications of the President‚Äôs intellectual property agenda. In addition, the Chief of Staff manages the day-to-day policy coordination process with the White House, Department of Commerce, and other federal agencies. Earlier in his career, Mr. McCommas was an Associate at Bracewell LLP in Houston, Texas, where he focused on intellectual property litigation, patent prosecution, and tech transactions. While in Houston he participated in the Houston Bar Association‚Äôs Pro Bono Legal Lines and Veterans Clinic, along with representing underserved communities before the USPTO and in various legal matters. He has a Bachelor of Science degree in electrical engineering from Grove City College, an M.A. in English from Georgetown University, and a J.D. from the University of Virginia School of Law, where he was on the editorial board of the Virginia Journal of Law and Technology.','U.S. Patent and Trademark Office via Internet Archive','https://web.archive.org/web/20180118225753/https://www.uspto.gov/about-us/executive-biographies/brendan-mccommas',NULL,'McCommas',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
    ('947','Commerce','John M. Cooney','Senior Advisor for Budget and Administration, International Trade Administration',NULL,NULL,'131767','2017-04-24 00:00:00',NULL,'https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4388475-John-M-Cooney-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'john-m-cooney',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'commerce','False',NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/john-cooney-3405594/','In his role as Senior Advisor for the Office of the Under Secretary for the International Trade Administration (ITA) within the U.S. Department of Commerce, John advises the Under Secretary on specific programs, policy, and administration matters. He works closely with ITA Senior Leadership. John recently served as the Budget and Administration Public Events Manager for the Presidential Inaugural Committee and prior to that was a partner at Minneapolis-based Fallbrook Communications','Small Business Administration via Internet Archive','https://web.archive.org/web/20180118191558/https://www.sba.gov/event/1579278',NULL,'Cooney',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
    ('979','Commerce','Christopher Wayne Oliver','Assistant Administrator for Marine Fisheries',NULL,NULL,'160000','2017-06-19 00:00:00',NULL,'https://www.documentcloud.org/documents/4387577-Christopher-Wayne-Oliver-Financial-Disclosure.html',NULL,NULL,NULL,15,'christopher-wayne-oliver',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'commerce',NULL,NULL,NULL,'https://www.linkedin.com/in/chris-oliver-022872b/detail/photo/','Oliver most recently served as Executive Director of the North Pacific Fishery Management Council, a position he held for the past 16 years. He has been with the Council since 1990, also serving as a fisheries biologist and then deputy director. During his tenure as executive director he led the way on several cutting edge management initiatives, including development of limited access privilege programs and fishery cooperatives and catch share programs, the North Pacific‚Äôs comprehensive onboard observer program, numerous bycatch reduction programs, extensive habitat protection measures, commercial and recreational allocation programs, and coastal community development programs. He was also responsible for all administrative and operational aspects of the Council process, and lead staffer for legislative and international issues.','National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration via Internet Archive','https://web.archive.org/web/20180119165446/http://www.nmfs.noaa.gov/stories/2017/06/19_new_asst_admin.html',NULL,'Oliver',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),
